aybar + SUB + 2x Play:1)"},{"label":"Apple Music only through Bluetooth"},{"label":"SAT Antenna"},{"label":"Speakers in Saloon & Cockpit, Flybridge, Bownet"},{"label":"TV set & Satellite"},{"label":"DVD / Blueray player"},{"label":"Internet WIFi"},{"label":"Wet bar"},{"label":"Sunpads"}],"toys":[{"label":"Water skies adult and for children"},{"label":"Wakeboard"},{"label":"Monoski"},{"label":"Kneeboard"},{"label":"Water tube"},{"label":"Towable ring"},{"label":"SUP","quantity":"2"},{"label":"Snorkeling Gear: Masks & flippers"},{"label":"Beach games"},{"label":"Floating mats"},{"label":"Fishing gear"},{"label":"Kayak"}],"entertainment":["Sonos Surround 5.1 (Playbar + SUB + 2x Play:1)","Apple Music only through Bluetooth","SAT Antenna","Speakers in Saloon & Cockpit, Flybridge, Bownet","TV set & Satellite","DVD / Blueray player","Internet WIFi"],"tenders":["Black Highfield Sport 420 Rib with Yamaha 60 hp outboard"]},"crew":[{"name":"Franko MIletić","avatar":"/media/media::image::a::vessel::d5cca38e-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::a44ae6e0-da91-11ef-8ed6-5ba77a2a409e/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"NATIONALITY / AGE / LANGUAGE\nCroatian / Born 1998 / ENGLISH, CROATIAN\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\nYacht Master License, all vessels up to 100GT, D2STCW Advance fighting D2STCW Basic Safety(STCW A-VI/1) Certificate. \n\nFranko is a young, highly skilled and versatile yacht captain with extensive experience in commanding a variety of vessels, including sailboats, catamarans, motor yachts, and speedboats up to 70ft. Having worked as a private skipper on luxury speedboats and led international boat deliveries, he excels in both navigating and operating yachts with precision. With a positive and hardworking approach, Franko is dedicated to fostering a professional and enjoyable environment, often taking on hosting duties when needed. Him, together with a hostess onboard Sunreef 50 SOLITAIRE, will provide a high level of service to guests..\n\nFAVOURITE PLACE ON THE ADRIATIC COAST\nFranko’s favourite place on the Adriatic coast is Korcula town and island of Proizd because of crystal clear blue waters and smell of the pine trees. He says his favourite water sport activity is fishing."},{"name":"Nina Zec","avatar":"/media/media::image::a::vessel::d5cca38e-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::e96a0fd0-da91-11ef-9154-b17440cd2445/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"NATIONALITY / AGE / LANGUAGE\nCroatian, / Born 2000 / ENGLISH, CROATIAN\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\nTrained Stewardess, ENG1 Medical Certificate\nD2 Basic Safety (STCW) Certificate.\n\nNina is a skilled boat hostess with extensive experience onluxury yachts like Lagoon, Hanse, and Azimut. Specializing in guest service, meal prep, and onboard operations, she ensures exceptional onboard experiences. Certified in STCW, Advanced Fire Training, and Medical Courses, Nina holds a B-category skipper license and has completed hostess training. Born on one of the most vibrant Croatian island Hvar, and working at the local restaurant, Nina gained experience in presenting the best Adriatic coast can offer through her cuisine and lifestyle. Fluent in English and Croatian (with basics of Italian and Spanish) she adapts seamlessly to diverse guest needs. Passionate, detail-oriented, and dedicated, Nina will bring a creative touch to every journey onboard Sunreef 50 SOLITAIRE. Her favourite water sport activity is swimming and snorkeling and favourite dish to make on board is Fish cooked in local Dalmatian style.\n\nFAVOURITE PLACE ON THE ADRIATIC COAST\nNina’s favourite place on the Adriatic coast is island of Vis, rich in nature and with eventful past which is seen through numerous monuments from ancient to recent times.."}],"pricing":{"weekPricingFrom":{"currency":"EUR","price":1750000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":1750000,"unit":"WEEK"},"weekPricingTo":{"currency":"EUR","price":3200000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":3200000,"unit":"WEEK"},"pricingInfo":[{"name":"Until April 25, 20